============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Empiricism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   All knowledge comes from sensory experience; mind is blank slate
Philosopher:  Locke/Hume
Example:      We know fire burns because we felt it, not through pure reason

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is a neuron?
A1: A neuron is a nerve cell that processes and transmits
     information through electrical and chemical signals.
     Key parts: dendrites (receive signals), cell body, axon
     (send signals).

Q2: What is a programming language?
A2: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q3: What is gravity?
A3: Gravity is an attractive force between all masses.
     Newton described it as F = Gm1m2/r². Einstein refined
     it as spacetime curvature in general relativity.

Q4: What is supply and demand?
A4: Supply and demand determines prices: higher demand or
     lower supply raises prices; lower demand or higher
     supply lowers prices. Equilibrium is where both curves
     intersect.

Q5: What is the Big Bang?
A5: The Big Bang theory states the universe began from an
     extremely hot, dense point approximately 13.8 billion
     years ago and has been expanding ever since.

